## 🗓️ Sprint 2 — Week 2: Core Food Detection

**Sprint Goal:** User uploads a meal photo → Gemini detects it → result saved to MealLogs.

| Who | Tasks (this week) |
|---|---|
| **Piyush** 🎯 | ① Improve the Gemini detection prompt: add few-shot Indian food examples (Dal Makhani, Biryani, Roti, Idli, Samosa etc. with calorie estimates) <br>② Handle edge cases in `food_detection.py`: multiple dishes, blurry images, non-food → graceful JSON fallback <br>③ Review M1's 20-food test report, refine prompt accordingly <br>*(~5 hrs total)* |
| **M1** | ① Run 20 diverse Indian food photos through Piyush's detector, log results in a spreadsheet (correct? calories accurate?) <br>② Write a `meal_type` auto-classifier addition to the prompt (breakfast/lunch/dinner/snack) <br>③ Add a confidence flag rule: if calorie estimate seems extreme → flag for user review |
| **M2** | ① Build Detection Screen — camera capture button + image upload fallback <br>② Loading spinner state while Gemini processes <br>③ Detection result card: food items list, macro table, total calories <br>④ "Save Meal" CTA → calls `POST /meal-logs` |
| **M3** | ① Build `POST /detect-meal` endpoint: receives image → calls Piyush's `food_detection.py` → returns JSON <br>② Build `POST /meal-logs` — save result to MealLogs <br>③ Build `GET /meal-logs/:user_id?date=` — fetch a day's meals <br>④ Set up image upload to Supabase Storage → return public URL |
| **M4** | ① Write test cases for `POST /detect-meal` (valid image, invalid image, empty body) <br>② Run M3's endpoint through Postman with 5 real food photos — report bugs <br>③ Add JWT middleware to protected routes (assist M3) |

**✅ Week 2 Demo:** Photo of Indian food → detected items + calories → saved to DB.

